<ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">president</ENAMEX>'s hands. But if <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">voters</ENAMEX> ignored the condition of the economy in
choosing their <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">president</ENAMEX>, they would be even less realistic.

            
So, with all those cautions in mind, I ask
again: Who deserves credit? In a recent column in the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Washington Post</ENAMEX> ,
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">James K. Glassman</ENAMEX> argues that <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Reagan</ENAMEX> should get it. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Reagan</ENAMEX>'s tax cuts, Glassman
