entrepreneurial culture. This is pretty far-fetched. Taking into account both
tax cuts and tax increases, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Reagan</ENAMEX> didn't reduce the overall tax burden during
his presidency. Supply-side dogma notwithstanding, what has boosted tax
revenues beyond expectations in <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">the last couple of years</TIMEX> are the last <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">two</NUMEX> tax
increases , in <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1990 and 1993</TIMEX>. (And in fact, the economy has reacted
better to increases than to cuts. See "<ENAMEX TYPE="WORK_OF_ART">The Best</ENAMEX>
Policy.") <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Reagan</ENAMEX>'s large spending increases for defense and the growth in
