<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">trade</ENAMEX>, and his reappointment of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Volcker</ENAMEX> in <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1983</TIMEX>. (Under pressure from
free-lunch <ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">Republicans</ENAMEX>, he declined to reappoint <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Volcker</ENAMEX> again in <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1987</TIMEX>, but
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">chose Alan Greenspan</ENAMEX>, who's been just as good, though under less challenging
